<br>
Long ago, when the Gods played and warred on Norrath itself, Ralolos Zek led an Army of Norrathian believers against another God, into the Plane of that God. Retribution on Norrath was severe.<br>
<br>
In order to control and in some small way protect those of us on Norrath that are not Gods, The Nameless BANISHED unrestricted access to Norrath to the Gods. They can not Directly come to nor touch Norrath. They were able to eventually learn a means to create (some of them anyway) a small &quot;plane&quot; to call theirs.<br>
<br>
On this &quot;plane&quot; they can have minions and they can appear in a weakened state , a &quot;shade&quot; of themselves. And at times, some of them have discovered a means to appear on Norrath itself, BUT that again is but a &quot;shade&quot; of the God.<br>
<br>
To deny the exsistance of the creators of the majority of the sentinent life on Norrath is HUBRIS.  Chose not to worship one, that is a decision left to the individual. But do not pretend to know that Gods do not exsist.<br>
<br>
As for the claim that if we but stop worshipping these Gods they will vanish...... They exsisted LONG before Norrath was discovered by Veeshan. They will exsist LONG after Norrath fades into a lifeless hulk of asteroid beaten earth.<br>
<br>
Every race except man can directly trace their exsistance to a God that CREATED the race. Man's creation is lost in the age he first appeared, no one knows for sure if he sprang forth on Norrath with out a God's intervention or if the God that created him just doesnt want anyone to know. Some say Man is an offshot of the Barbarian (man includes Erudite, since they came about from a split with man) some say an unknown God made them. I am sure some believers of some Gods claim they were made by that God. (one foolish worshipper of Karana makes such a claim here).<br>
<br>
To deny the facts of Gods exsistance is foolish indeed. Chose not to pay tribute to any, they will survive just fine without you. But do not be so foolish as to think you KNOW the true power of our Dieties. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukafesylvanblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kafe Sylvanblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/14/01 1:52:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The followers of Tunare</span><hr size=1> I do not understand this attack on we who worship Tunare.<br>
<br>
  Karana and Tunare are not at odds.  Rather they complement each other.  Tunare is the goddess of life and growth.  Karana is the god of storms.  The storms of Karana nourish and strengthen the children of Tunare while Karans followers also benifit from the fertile soils and energizing rays of sunshine that are the blessings of the mother.<br>
<br>
  Is it any wonder that the drow do shun her sunlight.<br>
<br>
  We who love the blessings of these natural partners have enough to worry about with those who would destroy these gifts without turning upon each other in a petty &quot;my god is better than your god&quot; squabble.<br>
<br>
Kafe,<br>
Tunare's Ranger of the 14th Hunt<br>
